<h2 id="what-is-pabau">💉 What Is Pabau?</h2>

Pabau is a UK-founded practice management platform built specifically for medical aesthetics, dermatology, and cosmetic clinics. Unlike generic salon software retrofitted for med spas, Pabau was designed from day one to handle clinical workflows: treatment consent forms, medical histories, before/after photo documentation, prescription tracking, and HIPAA-compliant charting.

The platform combines EMR functionality with operational tools most med spas need: online booking, automated marketing, inventory management, staff scheduling, and detailed financial reporting. This consolidation is the primary value proposition — instead of stitching together Vagaro for booking, Jane App for charting, Mailchimp for marketing, and a separate POS system, everything lives in one database.

Pabau entered the North American market aggressively in 2024 and has been iterating quickly based on operator feedback. The 2026 version addresses many complaints we had about the earlier builds, particularly around payment processing flexibility and multi-location reporting.

<h2 id="our-experience">🏢 Our Experience Managing Aesthetic Locations</h2>

Our team has collectively managed operations across 500+ aesthetic and wellness locations, from single-injector boutiques to 40+ location med spa chains. We've implemented Pabau at 23 locations over the past 18 months, ranging from standalone facial bars to full-service medical spas offering injectables, laser treatments, and body contouring.

The implementation pattern we've seen consistently: Pabau shines brightest at the 3-15 location range. Below that, the platform's depth can feel like overkill for simple operations. Above that, enterprise operators sometimes need custom integrations that require Pabau's API and development resources.

At one 8-location chain in Texas, we tracked a 34% reduction in administrative hours per location after full Pabau adoption. The biggest time savings came from eliminating manual consent form processing and automated treatment reminder sequences. Staff who previously spent 2+ hours daily on paperwork and follow-up communications redirected that time to revenue-generating activities.

The flip side: we've also seen implementations fail. A 2-location operation in Arizona abandoned Pabau after 4 months because they underestimated the training investment and never fully migrated from their legacy systems. Running parallel systems during transition is expensive and confusing — commit fully or don't start.

<h2 id="key-features">⚙️ Key Features</h2>

<h3>EMR & Clinical Documentation</h3>

Pabau's electronic medical records functionality is genuinely built for aesthetics. The treatment charting includes face/body mapping for injection sites, standardized templates for Botox/filler documentation, and integrated consent workflows that capture digital signatures with timestamps.

Photo documentation is seamless — the system prompts staff to capture before photos at check-in, stores them in the patient record with automatic date stamping, and makes comparison views available during follow-up appointments. This isn't a bolted-on feature; it's core to how consultations flow.

For prescription management, Pabau integrates with major e-prescribing networks. Providers can send prescriptions directly from the patient chart without switching systems. Medical history intake forms are fully customizable and can be sent to patients pre-appointment to reduce in-clinic wait times.

<h3>Online Booking & Deposits</h3>

The booking engine handles the complexity med spas face: treatment durations that vary by provider, equipment dependencies (one laser machine shared across providers), and required consultation steps before certain procedures.

Deposit collection at booking is where we've seen the biggest operational impact. Med spas collecting 20-50% deposits through Pabau's booking flow report no-show rates dropping from 15-20% to under 8%. The system handles partial payments, deposits applied to final invoices, and automatic refund processing for cancellations within policy windows.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Configure deposit requirements to escalate based on appointment value. We recommend 20% deposits for services under $300, 30% for $300-$1,000, and 50% for premium packages over $1,000. This protects revenue without creating friction for lower-ticket services.
</div>

<h3>Marketing Automation</h3>

Built-in email and SMS marketing removes the need for Mailchimp, Klaviyo, or similar tools for most operators. Sequences can trigger based on treatment history (send Botox refresh reminders at 10 weeks post-treatment), purchase behavior (target patients who bought skincare but haven't rebooked treatments), or engagement gaps (win-back campaigns for patients absent 6+ months).

The template library includes aesthetics-specific designs, and the segmentation capabilities are surprisingly robust for an all-in-one platform. You can build segments based on treatment types received, average transaction value, referral source, and dozens of other attributes.

<h3>Inventory & Retail Management</h3>

Tracking injectable units, skincare inventory, and retail products happens within the same system as clinical documentation. When a provider charts 40 units of Botox, inventory decrements automatically. When a patient purchases skincare at checkout, it syncs to the same transaction as their treatment.

Multi-location inventory visibility lets operators identify slow-moving products at specific locations and transfer stock before expiration. Reorder point alerts prevent stockouts on high-velocity items.

<h3>Multi-Location Reporting</h3>

The 2026 reporting dashboard finally delivers what multi-unit operators need: consolidated views with drill-down capability. See total revenue across all locations, then click into individual location performance, then into provider-level metrics.

Key reports we use weekly: revenue per treatment room hour, provider productivity comparisons, treatment mix analysis, and patient retention cohorts. All exportable to CSV for operators who need to manipulate data in Excel or feed into business intelligence tools.

